-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/gc.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":93,"character":15},"end":{"line":93,"character":21}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: metav1"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/gc_test.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/cleanup.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/client.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/errors.go":[]},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md\n@@ -708,5 +708,374 @@\n \n - [AR-006: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理](design.md)\n - [Expiration Logic](expiration.go)\n - [Cleanup Manager](cleanup.go)\n-- [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/garbage-collection/)\n\\ No newline at end of file\n+- [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/garbage-collection/)\n+\n+---\n+\n+# AR-038: Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager)\n+\n+- **AR ID**: AR-038\n+- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n+- **Language**: Go\n+- **Size**: L\n+- **Status**: ST-1 In Progress\n+\n+## 1. Overview\n+\n+This document provides technical implementation details for comprehensive Go unit tests in the workloadmanager module. The test suite covers all major components including WorkloadManager service, GC worker, expiration checker, graceful shutdown manager, cleanup manager, and the reconciler.\n+\n+## 2. Architecture Overview\n+\n+The `pkg/workloadmanager` module provides resource lifecycle management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources:\n+\n+| Component | File | Responsibility |\n+|-----------|------|----------------|\n+| WorkloadManager | `service.go` | CRUD operations, sandbox operations |\n+| GC Worker | `gc.go` | Periodic garbage collection (existing tests: 967 lines) |\n+| Expiration Checker | `expiration.go` | TTL, idle timeout, max lifetime logic |\n+| Graceful Manager | `graceful.go` | Connection draining, pre-delete hooks |\n+| Cleanup Manager | `cleanup.go` | Orphaned resource cleanup |\n+| K8s Client | `client.go` | Kubernetes client initialization |\n+| Reconciler | `reconciler/reconciler.go` | AgentRuntime reconciliation |\n+| Server | `server.go` | HTTP server initialization |\n+\n+### Test File Organization\n+\n+```\n+pkg/workloadmanager/\n+├── service_test.go           # WorkloadManager interface tests\n+├── client_test.go            # K8sClient initialization tests  \n+├── gc_test.go                # GC worker tests (EXISTING)\n+├── expiration_test.go        # Expiration checker tests (EXISTING)\n+├── graceful_test.go         # Graceful manager tests\n+├── cleanup_test.go          # Cleanup manager tests\n+├── delete_test.go           # Delete operation tests\n+├── server_test.go           # Server initialization tests\n+├── batch_test.go            # Batch operations tests\n+└── reconciler/\n+    ├── reconciler_test.go   # Reconciler tests\n+    └── errors_test.go       # Error handling tests\n+```\n+\n+## 3. Data Structures\n+\n+### Core Types (`types.go`)\n+```go\n+type Sandbox struct {\n+    Name           string\n+    Namespace      string\n+    SessionID      string\n+    State          SandboxState\n+    CreatedAt      time.Time\n+    ExpiresAt      *time.Time\n+    LastActivityAt *time.Time\n+    Labels         map[string]string\n+    Annotations    map[string]string\n+}\n+\n+type SandboxState string\n+const (\n+    SandboxStateUnknown  SandboxState = \"Unknown\"\n+    SandboxStatePending  SandboxState = \"Pending\"\n+    SandboxStateRunning  SandboxState = \"Running\"\n+    SandboxStateFailed   SandboxState = \"Failed\"\n+    SandboxStateDeleting SandboxState = \"Deleting\"\n+)\n+\n+type DeleteOptions struct {\n+    GracePeriodSeconds *int64\n+    Force              bool\n+    LabelSelector      string\n+    Preconditions      *Preconditions\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### Error Types\n+```go\n+var (\n+    ErrSandboxNotFound    = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n+    ErrDeletionFailed     = errors.New(\"deletion failed\")\n+    ErrStaleFinalizer     = errors.New(\"stale finalizer\")\n+    ErrOrphanedResource   = errors.New(\"orphaned resource\")\n+    ErrResourceNotFound   = errors.New(\"resource not found\")\n+    ErrResourceNotDeleted = errors.New(\"resource not deleted\")\n+)\n+```\n+\n+### Configuration Types\n+```go\n+type GCConfig struct {\n+    GCEnabled   bool\n+    GCInterval  time.Duration\n+    GCBatchSize int\n+}\n+\n+type ExpirationConfig struct {\n+    TTL         time.Duration\n+    IdleTimeout time.Duration\n+    MaxLifetime time.Duration\n+}\n+\n+type ReconcilerConfig struct {\n+    SyncInterval   time.Duration\n+    MaxRetries     int\n+    RetryDelays    time.Duration\n+    Namespace      string\n+    EnableMetrics  bool\n+    Workers        int\n+    RateLimitBurst int\n+    RateLimitQPS   float64\n+}\n+```\n+\n+## 4. API Contracts\n+\n+### WorkloadManager Interface (`service.go:15-39`)\n+```go\n+type WorkloadManager interface {\n+    // AgentRuntime CRUD\n+    CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, agentRuntime, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n+    GetAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n+    ListAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace, opts) (*AgentRuntimeList, error)\n+    UpdateAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, agentRuntime, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n+    DeleteAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name, opts) error\n+    GetAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, namespace, name, opts) (*AgentRuntimeStatus, error)\n+    PatchAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, namespace, name, pt, data, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n+    WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace, opts) (watch.Interface, error)\n+    \n+    // CodeInterpreter CRUD (same method pattern)\n+    \n+    // Sandbox operations\n+    DeleteSandbox(ctx, namespace, sessionID, opts) error\n+    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, namespace, sessionID) (*Sandbox, error)\n+    ListSandboxes(ctx, namespace, opts) (*SandboxList, error)\n+    \n+    Close() error\n+}\n+```\n+\n+### GC Worker Interface (`gc.go:59-70`)\n+```go\n+type GCWorker struct {\n+    client            versioned.Interface\n+    k8sClient         *kubernetes.Clientset\n+    config            *GCConfig\n+    stopCh            chan struct{}\n+    cleanupMgr        *CleanupManager\n+    expirationChecker *ExpirationChecker\n+    stats             GCStats\n+}\n+\n+func (g *GCWorker) Start(ctx context.Context)\n+func (g *GCWorker) Stop()\n+func (g *GCWorker) IsRunning() bool\n+func (g *GCWorker) GetConfig() *GCConfig\n+func (g *GCWorker) GetStats() GCStats\n+func (g *GCWorker) TriggerGCCycle(ctx) *GCResult\n+func (g *GCWorker) UpdateConfig(config *GCConfig)\n+```\n+\n+### Reconciler Interface (`reconciler/reconciler.go:128-169`)\n+```go\n+type AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n+    client         versioned.Interface\n+    k8sClient      *workloadmanager.K8sClient\n+    scheme         *runtime.Scheme\n+    recorder       record.EventRecorder\n+    config         *ReconcilerConfig\n+    metrics        *ReconcilerMetrics\n+}\n+\n+func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ReconcileRequest) (ReconcileResult, error)\n+```\n+\n+## 5. Testing Strategy\n+\n+### 5.1 Testing Approach\n+\n+**Unit Testing Principles:**\n+1. Use table-driven tests for parameterized scenarios\n+2. Mock external Kubernetes clients using fake clientsets\n+3. Test both success and error paths comprehensively\n+4. Verify state transitions and side effects\n+5. Ensure thread-safety for concurrent operations\n+\n+**Mock Strategy:**\n+- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake` for typed clients\n+- `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake` for Kubernetes clientset\n+- Custom mock interfaces for complex dependencies\n+\n+### 5.2 Test Utilities\n+\n+```go\n+// Test fixtures factory\n+func newTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace, sessionID string) *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n+\n+func newTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace, sessionID string) *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n+\n+func newTestSandbox(name, namespace, sessionID string, state SandboxState) *Sandbox\n+\n+// Mock clients\n+func newFakeClientset(agentRuntimes []*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, codeInterpreters []*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) versioned.Interface\n+\n+func newFakeK8sClient(pods []corev1.Pod, services []corev1.Service, configmaps []corev1.ConfigMap) *kubernetes.Clientset\n+```\n+\n+## 6. Implementation Details\n+\n+### 6.1 Service Tests (`service_test.go`)\n+\n+| Test Function | Description |\n+|---------------|-------------|\n+| `TestNewWorkloadManager` | Verify constructor creates valid instance |\n+| `TestCreateAgentRuntime_*` | Create with various inputs, validation errors |\n+| `TestGetAgentRuntime_*` | Found, not found, namespace errors |\n+| `TestListAgentRuntimes_*` | Empty list, multiple items, pagination |\n+| `TestUpdateAgentRuntime_*` | Successful update, not found, conflict |\n+| `TestDeleteAgentRuntime_*` | Successful deletion, not found, graceful period |\n+| `TestGetCodeInterpreter_*` | Same pattern as AgentRuntime |\n+| `TestDeleteCodeInterpreter_*` | Same pattern as AgentRuntime |\n+| `TestGetSandboxBySessionID_*` | AgentRuntime match, CodeInterpreter match, not found |\n+| `TestListSandboxes_*` | Combined list from both resource types |\n+| `TestDeleteSandbox_*` | Delete AgentRuntime, delete CodeInterpreter, not found |\n+| `TestSandboxConversions` | Verify sandboxFromAgentRuntime and sandboxFromCodeInterpreter |\n+\n+### 6.2 Cleanup Tests (`cleanup_test.go`)\n+\n+| Test Function | Description |\n+|---------------|-------------|\n+| `TestCleanupManager_New` | Constructor validation |\n+| `TestCleanupServices_*` | Services found/not found, owner reference matching |\n+| `TestCleanupConfigMaps_*` | ConfigMaps with auto-delete annotation |\n+| `TestCleanupPVCs_*` | PVCs with retain policy handling |\n+| `TestCleanupOrphanedResources_*` | Multiple resource types cleanup |\n+| `TestCleanupAllResources_*` | Full cleanup workflow |\n+| `TestFindOrphanedServices_*` | Orphan detection logic |\n+\n+### 6.3 Graceful Manager Tests (`graceful_test.go`)\n+\n+| Test Function | Description |\n+|---------------|-------------|\n+| `TestGracefulManager_New` | Constructor validation |\n+| `TestRegisterConnection_*` | Connection registration, concurrent access |\n+| `TestUnregisterConnection_*` | Connection unregistration |\n+| `TestIsDraining_*` | Drain state tracking |\n+| `TestGetActiveConnections_*` | Connection count |\n+| `TestWaitForConnections_*` | Timeout and success scenarios |\n+| `TestExecutePreDeleteHook_*` | Hook execution, timeout handling |\n+| `TestSendSIGTERM_*` | SIGTERM delivery, grace period handling |\n+| `TestExecuteGracefulDelete_*` | Full graceful deletion workflow |\n+\n+### 6.4 Client Tests (`client_test.go`)\n+\n+| Test Function | Description |\n+|---------------|-------------|\n+| `TestNewK8sClient_*` | In-cluster mode, kubeconfig mode, error handling |\n+| `TestNewInClusterClient_*` | Successful initialization |\n+| `TestExpandKubeconfigPath_*` | Tilde expansion, empty paths |\n+\n+### 6.5 Batch Operations Tests (`batch_test.go`)\n+\n+| Test Function | Description |\n+|---------------|-------------|\n+| `TestBatchDelete` | Multiple resource deletion with partial failures |\n+| `TestBatchList` | Combined listing with pagination |\n+\n+### 6.6 Server Tests (`server_test.go`)\n+\n+| Test Function | Description |\n+|---------------|-------------|\n+| `TestNewServer` | Server initialization with config |\n+| `TestServerStartStop` | Lifecycle management |\n+\n+### 6.7 Reconciler Tests (`reconciler/reconciler_test.go`)\n+\n+| Test Function | Description |\n+|---------------|-------------|\n+| `TestReconciler_New` | Constructor with default config |\n+| `TestReconciler_ReconcileCreate` | Create flow with pod/service/configmap |\n+| `TestReconciler_ReconcileUpdate` | Update flow with change detection |\n+| `TestReconciler_ReconcileDelete` | Delete flow with finalizer removal |\n+| `TestReconciler_HandleError` | Error classification and retry logic |\n+| `TestReconcilerMetrics_*` | Metrics collection and retrieval |\n+| `TestEnsureFinalizer_*` | Finalizer addition logic |\n+| `TestRemoveFinalizer_*` | Finalizer removal logic |\n+\n+### 6.8 Error Handling Tests (`reconciler/errors_test.go`)\n+\n+| Test Function | Description |\n+|---------------|-------------|\n+| `TestReconcilerErrorTypes` | All error type classifications |\n+| `TestIsRetryable` | Retryable error detection |\n+| `TestIsTerminal` | Terminal error detection |\n+| `TestErrorRegistry` | Error registration and retrieval |\n+| `TestNewReconcilerErrorFromK8s` | K8s error conversion |\n+\n+## 7. Error Handling Patterns\n+\n+### ReconcilerError Types (`reconciler/errors.go:10-18`)\n+```go\n+const (\n+    ErrorTypeTransient  ErrorType = \"Transient\"\n+    ErrorTypePermanent  ErrorType = \"Permanent\"\n+    ErrorTypeConflict   ErrorType = \"Conflict\"\n+    ErrorTypeNotFound   ErrorType = \"NotFound\"\n+    ErrorTypeValidation ErrorType = \"Validation\"\n+)\n+```\n+\n+### Error Test Cases\n+```go\n+func TestReconcilerErrorTypes(t *testing.T) {\n+    tests := []struct {\n+        name     string\n+        err      error\n+        wantType ErrorType\n+        wantRetry bool\n+    }{\n+        {\"transient error\", NewTransientError(\"timeout\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypeTransient, true},\n+        {\"permanent error\", NewPermanentError(\"quota\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypePermanent, false},\n+        {\"not found\", NewNotFoundError(\"missing\", \"Pod\"), ErrorTypeNotFound, false},\n+        {\"conflict\", NewConflictError(\"version\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypeConflict, true},\n+        {\"validation\", NewValidationError(\"invalid\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypeValidation, false},\n+    }\n+    // ...\n+}\n+```\n+\n+## 8. Running Tests\n+\n+```bash\n+# Run all workloadmanager tests\n+go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n+\n+# Run with coverage\n+go test -v -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n+\n+# Run specific test file\n+go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGCWorker\n+\n+# Run with race detector\n+go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n+\n+# Run reconciler tests\n+go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/...\n+```\n+\n+## 9. Acceptance Criteria\n+\n+1. **Coverage**: Minimum 70% line coverage for the module\n+2. **Test Quality**: All tests use table-driven approach where applicable\n+3. **Mocking**: External dependencies properly mocked (no real K8s API calls)\n+4. **Error Cases**: All error paths have corresponding test cases\n+5. **Concurrency**: Critical sections tested with goroutine safety\n+6. **Performance**: No tests have unnecessary sleeps or long timeouts\n+\n+## 10. Dependencies\n+\n+- `testing`: Standard Go testing package\n+- `github.com/stretchr/testify`: Assertions and test utilities\n+- `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake`: Fake Kubernetes clientset\n+- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake`: Fake typed clientset\n+- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1`: Test fixtures and helpers\n\\ No newline at end of file\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","before":"# AR-008: Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 (Sandbox GC Timing Cleanup Mechanism)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-008\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nThe Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) mechanism provides automatic periodic cleanup of expired sandboxes in the workloadmanager module. This feature extends the existing expiration logic in `expiration.go` by adding a scheduled GC worker that proactively identifies and removes expired resources, ensuring cluster resources are efficiently managed.\n\n## 2. Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── client.go              # Kubernetes client initialization (existing)\n├── service.go             # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n├── server.go              # HTTP server (existing)\n├── types.go               # Request/Response types (existing)\n├── expiration.go          # Expiration detection logic (existing)\n├── cleanup.go             # Resource cleanup handlers (existing)\n├── gc.go                  # NEW: GC worker and scheduler\n├── gc_test.go             # NEW: GC unit tests\n└── design.md              # This design document\n```\n\n### 2.2 Architecture Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     GC Scheduler                             │\n│              (golang.org/x/time/rate Ticker)                │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    GC Worker                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │\n│  │ ListExpired │→ │ Check State │→ │ Execute Delete  │   │\n│  │ Sandboxes   │  │ (finalizers)│  │ (with cleanup)  │   │\n│  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              WorkloadManager Service                         │\n│    (Expiration + Cleanup + Deletion operations)            │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## 3. Data Structures\n\n### 3.1 GC Configuration\n\n```go\n// GCConfig defines the garbage collection configuration.\ntype GCConfig struct {\n    // Interval is the time between GC cycles.\n    Interval time.Duration\n    \n    // BatchSize is the maximum number of sandboxes to process per cycle.\n    BatchSize int\n    \n    // MaxConcurrentDeletes is the maximum number of concurrent delete operations.\n    MaxConcurrentDeletes int\n    \n    // GracePeriod is the time to wait after deletion timestamp before forcing delete.\n    GracePeriod time.Duration\n    \n    // EnableMetrics enables metrics collection.\n    EnableMetrics bool\n}\n\n// DefaultGCConfig returns the default GC configuration.\nfunc DefaultGCConfig() *GCConfig {\n    return &GCConfig{\n        Interval:             5 * time.Minute,\n        BatchSize:            50,\n        MaxConcurrentDeletes: 10,\n        GracePeriod:          30 * time.Second,\n        EnableMetrics:        true,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 GC Worker\n\n```go\n// GCWorker performs periodic garbage collection of expired sandboxes.\ntype GCWorker struct {\n    client        versioned.Interface\n    k8sClient     *kubernetes.Clientset\n    config        *GCConfig\n    stopCh        chan struct{}\n    cleanupMgr    *CleanupManager\n    expirationChecker *ExpirationChecker\n}\n\n// NewGCWorker creates a new GC worker instance.\nfunc NewGCWorker(\n    client versioned.Interface,\n    k8sClient *kubernetes.Clientset,\n    config *GCConfig,\n) *GCWorker {\n    if config == nil {\n        config = DefaultGCConfig()\n    }\n    \n    return &GCWorker{\n        client:             client,\n        k8sClient:          k8sClient,\n        config:             config,\n        stopCh:             make(chan struct{}),\n        cleanupMgr:         NewCleanupManager(k8sClient),\n        expirationChecker:  NewExpirationChecker(nil),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 GC Result\n\n```go\n// GCResult contains the results of a GC cycle.\ntype GCResult struct {\n    // ScannedCount is the number of sandboxes scanned.\n    ScannedCount int `json:\"scannedCount\"`\n    \n    // ExpiredCount is the number of sandboxes identified as expired.\n    ExpiredCount int `json:\"expiredCount\"`\n    \n    // DeletedCount is the number of sandboxes successfully deleted.\n    DeletedCount int `json:\"deletedCount\"`\n    \n    // FailedCount is the number of sandboxes that failed to delete.\n    FailedCount int `json:\"failedCount\"`\n    \n    // Duration is the time taken for the GC cycle.\n    Duration time.Duration `json:\"duration\"`\n    \n    // Errors contains any errors encountered during the cycle.\n    Errors []string `json:\"errors,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 3.4 GC Statistics\n\n```go\n// GCStats holds garbage collection statistics.\ntype GCStats struct {\n    // TotalCycles is the total number of GC cycles run.\n    TotalCycles int64\n    \n    // TotalDeleted is the total number of sandboxes deleted.\n    TotalDeleted int64\n    \n    // TotalFailed is the total number of deletions that failed.\n    TotalFailed int64\n    \n    // LastRunTime is the time of the last GC run.\n    LastRunTime *metav1.Time\n    \n    // LastResult contains the result of the last GC cycle.\n    LastResult *GCResult\n}\n```\n\n## 4. API Contracts\n\n### 4.1 GC Control Endpoints\n\n| Operation | Method | Resource Path | Description |\n|-----------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n| Trigger GC | POST | /api/v1/gc/trigger | Manually trigger a GC cycle |\n| Get GC Status | GET | /api/v1/gc/status | Get GC worker status and statistics |\n| Update GC Config | PUT | /api/v1/gc/config | Update GC configuration |\n\n### 4.2 GC Response Types\n\n```go\n// GCTriggerResponse is the response to a GC trigger request.\ntype GCTriggerResponse struct {\n    // Started indicates whether the GC cycle was started.\n    Started bool `json:\"started\"`\n    \n    // Message provides additional information.\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n}\n\n// GCStatusResponse is the response to a GC status request.\ntype GCStatusResponse struct {\n    // Running indicates if GC worker is running.\n    Running bool `json:\"running\"`\n    \n    // Config contains the current GC configuration.\n    Config *GCConfig `json:\"config\"`\n    \n    // Stats contains GC statistics.\n    Stats *GCStats `json:\"stats\"`\n    \n    // LastError contains the last error encountered.\n    LastError string `json:\"lastError,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// GCConfigUpdateRequest is a request to update GC configuration.\ntype GCConfigUpdateRequest struct {\n    // Interval is the new interval between GC cycles.\n    Interval string `json:\"interval,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // BatchSize is the new batch size.\n    BatchSize *int `json:\"batchSize,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // MaxConcurrentDeletes is the new max concurrent deletes.\n    MaxConcurrentDeletes *int `json:\"maxConcurrentDeletes,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // GracePeriod is the new grace period.\n    GracePeriod string `json:\"gracePeriod,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n## 5. Implementation Details\n\n### 5.1 GC Worker Lifecycle\n\n```go\n// Start begins the GC worker.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) Start(ctx context.Context) {\n    klog.InfoS(\"Starting GC worker\", \"interval\", g.config.Interval)\n    \n    ticker := time.NewTicker(g.config.Interval)\n    defer ticker.Stop()\n    \n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            klog.InfoS(\"GC worker stopping due to context cancellation\")\n            return\n        case <-g.stopCh:\n            klog.InfoS(\"GC worker stopping\")\n            return\n        case <-ticker.C:\n            g.runGCCycle(ctx)\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// Stop stops the GC worker.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) Stop() {\n    close(g.stopCh)\n}\n```\n\n### 5.2 GC Cycle Execution\n\n```go\n// runGCCycle executes a single garbage collection cycle.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) runGCCycle(ctx context.Context) {\n    startTime := time.Now()\n    result := &GCResult{}\n    \n    klog.V(4).InfoS(\"Starting GC cycle\")\n    \n    namespaces, err := g.getNamespaces(ctx)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to get namespaces\")\n        result.Errors = append(result.Errors, err.Error())\n        g.recordGCResult(result, startTime)\n        return\n    }\n    \n    result.ScannedCount = len(namespaces)\n    \n    for _, ns := range namespaces {\n        if err := g.processNamespace(ctx, ns, result); err != nil {\n            klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to process namespace\", \"namespace\", ns)\n            result.Errors = append(result.Errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", ns, err))\n        }\n        \n        if result.ScannedCount >= g.config.BatchSize {\n            klog.V(4).InfoS(\"Batch size reached\", \"scanned\", result.ScannedCount)\n            break\n        }\n    }\n    \n    result.Duration = time.Since(startTime)\n    g.recordGCResult(result, startTime)\n    \n    klog.InfoS(\"GC cycle completed\",\n        \"scanned\", result.ScannedCount,\n        \"expired\", result.ExpiredCount,\n        \"deleted\", result.DeletedCount,\n        \"failed\", result.FailedCount,\n        \"duration\", result.Duration)\n}\n```\n\n### 5.3 Namespace Processing\n\n```go\n// processNamespace processes expired sandboxes in a namespace.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) processNamespace(ctx context.Context, namespace string, result *GCResult) error {\n    // List AgentRuntimes\n    arList, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list agentruntimes: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // List CodeInterpreters\n    ciList, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list codeinterpreters: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Check each AgentRuntime for expiration\n    for i := range arList.Items {\n        ar := &arList.Items[i]\n        result.ScannedCount++\n        \n        if g.isExpired(ar) {\n            result.ExpiredCount++\n            if err := g.deleteAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, ar.Name); err != nil {\n                result.FailedCount++\n                result.Errors = append(result.Errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"agentruntime/%s: %v\", ar.Name, err))\n                klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to delete expired agentruntime\", \"name\", ar.Name)\n            } else {\n                result.DeletedCount++\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Check each CodeInterpreter for expiration\n    for i := range ciList.Items {\n        ci := &ciList.Items[i]\n        result.ScannedCount++\n        \n        if g.isExpired(ci) {\n            result.ExpiredCount++\n            if err := g.deleteCodeInterpreter(ctx, namespace, ci.Name); err != nil {\n                result.FailedCount++\n                result.Errors = append(result.Errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"codeinterpreter/%s: %v\", ci.Name, err))\n                klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to delete expired codeinterpreter\", \"name\", ci.Name)\n            } else {\n                result.DeletedCount++\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### 5.4 Expiration Detection\n\n```go\n// isExpired checks if an AgentRuntime is expired.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) isExpired(ar *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) bool {\n    sandbox := &Sandbox{\n        Name:        ar.Name,\n        Namespace:   ar.Namespace,\n        SessionID:   ar.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n        CreatedAt:   ar.CreationTimestamp.Time,\n        LastActivityAt: g.getLastActivityTime(ar),\n    }\n    \n    // Check if being deleted\n    if ar.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n        return true\n    }\n    \n    return g.expirationChecker.IsExpired(sandbox)\n}\n\n// isExpired checks if a CodeInterpreter is expired.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) isExpired(ci *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) bool {\n    sandbox := &Sandbox{\n        Name:        ci.Name,\n        Namespace:   ci.Namespace,\n        SessionID:   ci.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n        CreatedAt:   ci.CreationTimestamp.Time,\n        LastActivityAt: g.getLastActivityTime(ci),\n    }\n    \n    // Check if being deleted\n    if ci.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n        return true\n    }\n    \n    return g.expirationChecker.IsExpired(sandbox)\n}\n\n// getLastActivityTime extracts the last activity time from annotations.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) getLastActivityTime(obj metav1.Object) *time.Time {\n    annotations := obj.GetAnnotations()\n    if annotations == nil {\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    lastActivityStr := annotations[\"last-activity-time\"]\n    if lastActivityStr == \"\" {\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    t, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    return &t\n}\n```\n\n### 5.5 Deletion with Cleanup\n\n```go\n// deleteAgentRuntime deletes an AgentRuntime and its associated resources.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) deleteAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error {\n    // Get the resource to find associated resources\n    ar, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n            return nil // Already deleted\n        }\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    // Clean up orphaned resources\n    sandbox := &Sandbox{\n        Name:      ar.Name,\n        Namespace: ar.Namespace,\n        SessionID: ar.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n    }\n    \n    if _, err := g.cleanupMgr.CleanupAllResources(ctx, sandbox); err != nil {\n        klog.V(2).InfoS(\"Error cleaning up resources\", \"error\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Delete the resource\n    deleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{}\n    if g.config.GracePeriod > 0 {\n        gracePeriod := int64(g.config.GracePeriod.Seconds())\n        deleteOpts.GracePeriodSeconds = &gracePeriod\n    }\n    \n    return g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, name, deleteOpts)\n}\n\n// deleteCodeInterpreter deletes a CodeInterpreter and its associated resources.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) deleteCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error {\n    // Similar to deleteAgentRuntime\n    ci, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n            return nil\n        }\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    sandbox := &Sandbox{\n        Name:      ci.Name,\n        Namespace: ci.Namespace,\n        SessionID: ci.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n    }\n    \n    if _, err := g.cleanupMgr.CleanupAllResources(ctx, sandbox); err != nil {\n        klog.V(2).InfoS(\"Error cleaning up resources\", \"error\", err)\n    }\n    \n    deleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{}\n    if g.config.GracePeriod > 0 {\n        gracePeriod := int64(g.config.GracePeriod.Seconds())\n        deleteOpts.GracePeriodSeconds = &gracePeriod\n    }\n    \n    return g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete(ctx, name, deleteOpts)\n}\n```\n\n### 5.6 Integration with Server\n\n```go\n// GCServer wraps the GC worker with HTTP handlers.\ntype GCServer struct {\n    worker *GCWorker\n    stats  atomic.Value // stores *GCStats\n}\n\n// NewGCServer creates a new GC server.\nfunc NewGCServer(worker *GCWorker) *GCServer {\n    gs := &GCServer{\n        worker: worker,\n    }\n    gs.stats.Store(&GCStats{})\n    return gs\n}\n\n// RegisterRoutes registers GC routes on the router.\nfunc (gs *GCServer) RegisterRoutes(router *gin.RouterGroup) {\n    gc := router.Group(\"/gc\")\n    {\n        gc.POST(\"/trigger\", gs.handleTrigger)\n        gc.GET(\"/status\", gs.handleStatus)\n        gc.PUT(\"/config\", gs.handleConfigUpdate)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (gs *GCServer) handleTrigger(c *gin.Context) {\n    select {\n    case gs.worker.triggerCh <- struct{}{}:\n        c.JSON(http.StatusOK, GCTriggerResponse{\n            Started: true,\n            Message: \"GC cycle triggered\",\n        })\n    default:\n        c.JSON(http.StatusServiceUnavailable, GCTriggerResponse{\n            Started: false,\n            Message: \"GC cycle already in progress\",\n        })\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (gs *GCServer) handleStatus(c *gin.Context) {\n    stats := gs.stats.Load().(*GCStats)\n    \n    c.JSON(http.StatusOK, GCStatusResponse{\n        Running: gs.worker.IsRunning(),\n        Config:  gs.worker.GetConfig(),\n        Stats:   stats,\n    })\n}\n\nfunc (gs *GCServer) handleConfigUpdate(c *gin.Context) {\n    var req GCConfigUpdateRequest\n    if err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n        c.JSON(http.StatusBadRequest, NewAPIError(err.Error(), \"BadRequest\", http.StatusBadRequest))\n        return\n    }\n    \n    gs.worker.UpdateConfig(req)\n    \n    c.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"message\": \"GC configuration updated\"})\n}\n```\n\n## 6. Error Handling\n\n### 6.1 Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrGCWorkerNotRunning = errors.New(\"GC worker is not running\")\n    ErrGCAlreadyRunning   = errors.New(\"GC cycle already in progress\")\n    ErrInvalidConfig      = errors.New(\"invalid GC configuration\")\n    ErrNamespaceListFailed = errors.New(\"failed to list namespaces\")\n)\n```\n\n### 6.2 Error Handling Strategy\n\n| Scenario | Handling |\n|----------|----------|\n| Kubernetes API error | Log error, continue with next resource |\n| Resource already deleted | Skip, no error |\n| Cleanup failure | Log, continue deletion |\n| Batch size reached | Stop processing, report partial results |\n| Context cancelled | Stop gracefully, record partial results |\n\n## 7. Testing Strategy\n\n### 7.1 Unit Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestGCWorkerIsExpired(t *testing.T) {\n    worker := NewGCWorker(nil, nil, nil)\n    \n    // Test expired AgentRuntime\n    ar := &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:              \"test-ar\",\n            Namespace:         \"default\",\n            CreationTimestamp: metav1.Time{Time: time.Now().Add(-10 * time.Hour)},\n            DeletionTimestamp: &metav1.Time{Time: time.Now()},\n        },\n    }\n    \n    if !worker.isExpired(ar) {\n        t.Error(\"Expected expired AgentRuntime to be marked as expired\")\n    }\n    \n    // Test non-expired AgentRuntime\n    ar = &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:              \"test-ar-2\",\n            Namespace:         \"default\",\n            CreationTimestamp: metav1.Time{Time: time.Now()},\n        },\n    }\n    \n    if worker.isExpired(ar) {\n        t.Error(\"Expected non-expired AgentRuntime to not be marked as expired\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestGCWorkerGetNamespaces(t *testing.T) {\n    // Test namespace listing logic\n}\n\nfunc TestGCConfigValidation(t *testing.T) {\n    // Test config validation\n}\n```\n\n### 7.2 Test Coverage Targets\n\n| Component | Target Coverage |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| gc.go | 80% |\n| Integration with cleanup | 75% |\n\n## 8. Configuration\n\n### 8.1 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| GC_INTERVAL | 5m | Interval between GC cycles |\n| GC_BATCH_SIZE | 50 | Maximum sandboxes processed per cycle |\n| GC_MAX_CONCURRENT_DELETES | 10 | Maximum concurrent delete operations |\n| GC_GRACE_PERIOD | 30s | Grace period before force delete |\n| GC_ENABLED | true | Enable/disable GC worker |\n\n### 8.2 Server Configuration Extension\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    \n    // GCConfig is the garbage collection configuration.\n    GCConfig *GCConfig\n}\n```\n\n## 9. Metrics\n\n### 9.1 Prometheus Metrics\n\n| Metric | Type | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| gc_cycle_duration_seconds | Histogram | Duration of GC cycle |\n| gc_sandboxes_scanned_total | Counter | Total sandboxes scanned |\n| gc_sandboxes_expired_total | Counter | Total sandboxes identified as expired |\n| gc_sandboxes_deleted_total | Counter | Total sandboxes deleted |\n| gc_sandboxes_failed_total | Counter | Total deletion failures |\n\n### 9.2 Logging\n\n| Level | Scenario |\n|-------|----------|\n| V(4) | GC cycle start/completion |\n| V(2) | Individual deletion failures |\n| V(1) | Configuration changes |\n\n## 10. Dependencies\n\n### 10.1 Internal Dependencies\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned | Client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager (expiration.go) | Expiration detection |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager (cleanup.go) | Resource cleanup |\n\n### 10.2 External Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| k8s.io/client-go | Kubernetes client |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery | API types |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | Logging |\n| github.com/gin-gonic/gin | HTTP framework |\n\n## 11. Security Considerations\n\n### 11.1 RBAC Requirements\n\n```yaml\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"services\", \"configmaps\", \"persistentvolumeclaims\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"namespaces\"]\n  verbs: [\"list\", \"get\"]\n```\n\n### 11.2 Safety Measures\n\n- Batch processing prevents overwhelming the API server\n- Configurable concurrency limits\n- Grace period before force deletion\n- Logging of all deletion operations\n\n## 12. References\n\n- [AR-006: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理](design.md)\n- [Expiration Logic](expiration.go)\n- [Cleanup Manager](cleanup.go)\n- [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/garbage-collection/)","after":"# AR-008: Sandbox GC 定时清理机制 (Sandbox GC Timing Cleanup Mechanism)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-008\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nThe Sandbox GC (Garbage Collection) mechanism provides automatic periodic cleanup of expired sandboxes in the workloadmanager module. This feature extends the existing expiration logic in `expiration.go` by adding a scheduled GC worker that proactively identifies and removes expired resources, ensuring cluster resources are efficiently managed.\n\n## 2. Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── client.go              # Kubernetes client initialization (existing)\n├── service.go             # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n├── server.go              # HTTP server (existing)\n├── types.go               # Request/Response types (existing)\n├── expiration.go          # Expiration detection logic (existing)\n├── cleanup.go             # Resource cleanup handlers (existing)\n├── gc.go                  # NEW: GC worker and scheduler\n├── gc_test.go             # NEW: GC unit tests\n└── design.md              # This design document\n```\n\n### 2.2 Architecture Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     GC Scheduler                             │\n│              (golang.org/x/time/rate Ticker)                │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    GC Worker                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐   │\n│  │ ListExpired │→ │ Check State │→ │ Execute Delete  │   │\n│  │ Sandboxes   │  │ (finalizers)│  │ (with cleanup)  │   │\n│  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              WorkloadManager Service                         │\n│    (Expiration + Cleanup + Deletion operations)            │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## 3. Data Structures\n\n### 3.1 GC Configuration\n\n```go\n// GCConfig defines the garbage collection configuration.\ntype GCConfig struct {\n    // Interval is the time between GC cycles.\n    Interval time.Duration\n    \n    // BatchSize is the maximum number of sandboxes to process per cycle.\n    BatchSize int\n    \n    // MaxConcurrentDeletes is the maximum number of concurrent delete operations.\n    MaxConcurrentDeletes int\n    \n    // GracePeriod is the time to wait after deletion timestamp before forcing delete.\n    GracePeriod time.Duration\n    \n    // EnableMetrics enables metrics collection.\n    EnableMetrics bool\n}\n\n// DefaultGCConfig returns the default GC configuration.\nfunc DefaultGCConfig() *GCConfig {\n    return &GCConfig{\n        Interval:             5 * time.Minute,\n        BatchSize:            50,\n        MaxConcurrentDeletes: 10,\n        GracePeriod:          30 * time.Second,\n        EnableMetrics:        true,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 GC Worker\n\n```go\n// GCWorker performs periodic garbage collection of expired sandboxes.\ntype GCWorker struct {\n    client        versioned.Interface\n    k8sClient     *kubernetes.Clientset\n    config        *GCConfig\n    stopCh        chan struct{}\n    cleanupMgr    *CleanupManager\n    expirationChecker *ExpirationChecker\n}\n\n// NewGCWorker creates a new GC worker instance.\nfunc NewGCWorker(\n    client versioned.Interface,\n    k8sClient *kubernetes.Clientset,\n    config *GCConfig,\n) *GCWorker {\n    if config == nil {\n        config = DefaultGCConfig()\n    }\n    \n    return &GCWorker{\n        client:             client,\n        k8sClient:          k8sClient,\n        config:             config,\n        stopCh:             make(chan struct{}),\n        cleanupMgr:         NewCleanupManager(k8sClient),\n        expirationChecker:  NewExpirationChecker(nil),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.3 GC Result\n\n```go\n// GCResult contains the results of a GC cycle.\ntype GCResult struct {\n    // ScannedCount is the number of sandboxes scanned.\n    ScannedCount int `json:\"scannedCount\"`\n    \n    // ExpiredCount is the number of sandboxes identified as expired.\n    ExpiredCount int `json:\"expiredCount\"`\n    \n    // DeletedCount is the number of sandboxes successfully deleted.\n    DeletedCount int `json:\"deletedCount\"`\n    \n    // FailedCount is the number of sandboxes that failed to delete.\n    FailedCount int `json:\"failedCount\"`\n    \n    // Duration is the time taken for the GC cycle.\n    Duration time.Duration `json:\"duration\"`\n    \n    // Errors contains any errors encountered during the cycle.\n    Errors []string `json:\"errors,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### 3.4 GC Statistics\n\n```go\n// GCStats holds garbage collection statistics.\ntype GCStats struct {\n    // TotalCycles is the total number of GC cycles run.\n    TotalCycles int64\n    \n    // TotalDeleted is the total number of sandboxes deleted.\n    TotalDeleted int64\n    \n    // TotalFailed is the total number of deletions that failed.\n    TotalFailed int64\n    \n    // LastRunTime is the time of the last GC run.\n    LastRunTime *metav1.Time\n    \n    // LastResult contains the result of the last GC cycle.\n    LastResult *GCResult\n}\n```\n\n## 4. API Contracts\n\n### 4.1 GC Control Endpoints\n\n| Operation | Method | Resource Path | Description |\n|-----------|--------|---------------|-------------|\n| Trigger GC | POST | /api/v1/gc/trigger | Manually trigger a GC cycle |\n| Get GC Status | GET | /api/v1/gc/status | Get GC worker status and statistics |\n| Update GC Config | PUT | /api/v1/gc/config | Update GC configuration |\n\n### 4.2 GC Response Types\n\n```go\n// GCTriggerResponse is the response to a GC trigger request.\ntype GCTriggerResponse struct {\n    // Started indicates whether the GC cycle was started.\n    Started bool `json:\"started\"`\n    \n    // Message provides additional information.\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n}\n\n// GCStatusResponse is the response to a GC status request.\ntype GCStatusResponse struct {\n    // Running indicates if GC worker is running.\n    Running bool `json:\"running\"`\n    \n    // Config contains the current GC configuration.\n    Config *GCConfig `json:\"config\"`\n    \n    // Stats contains GC statistics.\n    Stats *GCStats `json:\"stats\"`\n    \n    // LastError contains the last error encountered.\n    LastError string `json:\"lastError,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// GCConfigUpdateRequest is a request to update GC configuration.\ntype GCConfigUpdateRequest struct {\n    // Interval is the new interval between GC cycles.\n    Interval string `json:\"interval,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // BatchSize is the new batch size.\n    BatchSize *int `json:\"batchSize,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // MaxConcurrentDeletes is the new max concurrent deletes.\n    MaxConcurrentDeletes *int `json:\"maxConcurrentDeletes,omitempty\"`\n    \n    // GracePeriod is the new grace period.\n    GracePeriod string `json:\"gracePeriod,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n## 5. Implementation Details\n\n### 5.1 GC Worker Lifecycle\n\n```go\n// Start begins the GC worker.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) Start(ctx context.Context) {\n    klog.InfoS(\"Starting GC worker\", \"interval\", g.config.Interval)\n    \n    ticker := time.NewTicker(g.config.Interval)\n    defer ticker.Stop()\n    \n    for {\n        select {\n        case <-ctx.Done():\n            klog.InfoS(\"GC worker stopping due to context cancellation\")\n            return\n        case <-g.stopCh:\n            klog.InfoS(\"GC worker stopping\")\n            return\n        case <-ticker.C:\n            g.runGCCycle(ctx)\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n// Stop stops the GC worker.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) Stop() {\n    close(g.stopCh)\n}\n```\n\n### 5.2 GC Cycle Execution\n\n```go\n// runGCCycle executes a single garbage collection cycle.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) runGCCycle(ctx context.Context) {\n    startTime := time.Now()\n    result := &GCResult{}\n    \n    klog.V(4).InfoS(\"Starting GC cycle\")\n    \n    namespaces, err := g.getNamespaces(ctx)\n    if err != nil {\n        klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to get namespaces\")\n        result.Errors = append(result.Errors, err.Error())\n        g.recordGCResult(result, startTime)\n        return\n    }\n    \n    result.ScannedCount = len(namespaces)\n    \n    for _, ns := range namespaces {\n        if err := g.processNamespace(ctx, ns, result); err != nil {\n            klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to process namespace\", \"namespace\", ns)\n            result.Errors = append(result.Errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", ns, err))\n        }\n        \n        if result.ScannedCount >= g.config.BatchSize {\n            klog.V(4).InfoS(\"Batch size reached\", \"scanned\", result.ScannedCount)\n            break\n        }\n    }\n    \n    result.Duration = time.Since(startTime)\n    g.recordGCResult(result, startTime)\n    \n    klog.InfoS(\"GC cycle completed\",\n        \"scanned\", result.ScannedCount,\n        \"expired\", result.ExpiredCount,\n        \"deleted\", result.DeletedCount,\n        \"failed\", result.FailedCount,\n        \"duration\", result.Duration)\n}\n```\n\n### 5.3 Namespace Processing\n\n```go\n// processNamespace processes expired sandboxes in a namespace.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) processNamespace(ctx context.Context, namespace string, result *GCResult) error {\n    // List AgentRuntimes\n    arList, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list agentruntimes: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // List CodeInterpreters\n    ciList, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to list codeinterpreters: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Check each AgentRuntime for expiration\n    for i := range arList.Items {\n        ar := &arList.Items[i]\n        result.ScannedCount++\n        \n        if g.isExpired(ar) {\n            result.ExpiredCount++\n            if err := g.deleteAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, ar.Name); err != nil {\n                result.FailedCount++\n                result.Errors = append(result.Errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"agentruntime/%s: %v\", ar.Name, err))\n                klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to delete expired agentruntime\", \"name\", ar.Name)\n            } else {\n                result.DeletedCount++\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Check each CodeInterpreter for expiration\n    for i := range ciList.Items {\n        ci := &ciList.Items[i]\n        result.ScannedCount++\n        \n        if g.isExpired(ci) {\n            result.ExpiredCount++\n            if err := g.deleteCodeInterpreter(ctx, namespace, ci.Name); err != nil {\n                result.FailedCount++\n                result.Errors = append(result.Errors, fmt.Sprintf(\"codeinterpreter/%s: %v\", ci.Name, err))\n                klog.ErrorS(err, \"Failed to delete expired codeinterpreter\", \"name\", ci.Name)\n            } else {\n                result.DeletedCount++\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### 5.4 Expiration Detection\n\n```go\n// isExpired checks if an AgentRuntime is expired.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) isExpired(ar *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) bool {\n    sandbox := &Sandbox{\n        Name:        ar.Name,\n        Namespace:   ar.Namespace,\n        SessionID:   ar.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n        CreatedAt:   ar.CreationTimestamp.Time,\n        LastActivityAt: g.getLastActivityTime(ar),\n    }\n    \n    // Check if being deleted\n    if ar.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n        return true\n    }\n    \n    return g.expirationChecker.IsExpired(sandbox)\n}\n\n// isExpired checks if a CodeInterpreter is expired.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) isExpired(ci *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) bool {\n    sandbox := &Sandbox{\n        Name:        ci.Name,\n        Namespace:   ci.Namespace,\n        SessionID:   ci.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n        CreatedAt:   ci.CreationTimestamp.Time,\n        LastActivityAt: g.getLastActivityTime(ci),\n    }\n    \n    // Check if being deleted\n    if ci.DeletionTimestamp != nil {\n        return true\n    }\n    \n    return g.expirationChecker.IsExpired(sandbox)\n}\n\n// getLastActivityTime extracts the last activity time from annotations.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) getLastActivityTime(obj metav1.Object) *time.Time {\n    annotations := obj.GetAnnotations()\n    if annotations == nil {\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    lastActivityStr := annotations[\"last-activity-time\"]\n    if lastActivityStr == \"\" {\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    t, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil\n    }\n    \n    return &t\n}\n```\n\n### 5.5 Deletion with Cleanup\n\n```go\n// deleteAgentRuntime deletes an AgentRuntime and its associated resources.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) deleteAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error {\n    // Get the resource to find associated resources\n    ar, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n            return nil // Already deleted\n        }\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    // Clean up orphaned resources\n    sandbox := &Sandbox{\n        Name:      ar.Name,\n        Namespace: ar.Namespace,\n        SessionID: ar.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n    }\n    \n    if _, err := g.cleanupMgr.CleanupAllResources(ctx, sandbox); err != nil {\n        klog.V(2).InfoS(\"Error cleaning up resources\", \"error\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Delete the resource\n    deleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{}\n    if g.config.GracePeriod > 0 {\n        gracePeriod := int64(g.config.GracePeriod.Seconds())\n        deleteOpts.GracePeriodSeconds = &gracePeriod\n    }\n    \n    return g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete(ctx, name, deleteOpts)\n}\n\n// deleteCodeInterpreter deletes a CodeInterpreter and its associated resources.\nfunc (g *GCWorker) deleteCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, namespace, name string) error {\n    // Similar to deleteAgentRuntime\n    ci, err := g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n    if err != nil {\n        if apierrors.IsNotFound(err) {\n            return nil\n        }\n        return err\n    }\n    \n    sandbox := &Sandbox{\n        Name:      ci.Name,\n        Namespace: ci.Namespace,\n        SessionID: ci.Labels[\"sessionId\"],\n    }\n    \n    if _, err := g.cleanupMgr.CleanupAllResources(ctx, sandbox); err != nil {\n        klog.V(2).InfoS(\"Error cleaning up resources\", \"error\", err)\n    }\n    \n    deleteOpts := metav1.DeleteOptions{}\n    if g.config.GracePeriod > 0 {\n        gracePeriod := int64(g.config.GracePeriod.Seconds())\n        deleteOpts.GracePeriodSeconds = &gracePeriod\n    }\n    \n    return g.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete(ctx, name, deleteOpts)\n}\n```\n\n### 5.6 Integration with Server\n\n```go\n// GCServer wraps the GC worker with HTTP handlers.\ntype GCServer struct {\n    worker *GCWorker\n    stats  atomic.Value // stores *GCStats\n}\n\n// NewGCServer creates a new GC server.\nfunc NewGCServer(worker *GCWorker) *GCServer {\n    gs := &GCServer{\n        worker: worker,\n    }\n    gs.stats.Store(&GCStats{})\n    return gs\n}\n\n// RegisterRoutes registers GC routes on the router.\nfunc (gs *GCServer) RegisterRoutes(router *gin.RouterGroup) {\n    gc := router.Group(\"/gc\")\n    {\n        gc.POST(\"/trigger\", gs.handleTrigger)\n        gc.GET(\"/status\", gs.handleStatus)\n        gc.PUT(\"/config\", gs.handleConfigUpdate)\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (gs *GCServer) handleTrigger(c *gin.Context) {\n    select {\n    case gs.worker.triggerCh <- struct{}{}:\n        c.JSON(http.StatusOK, GCTriggerResponse{\n            Started: true,\n            Message: \"GC cycle triggered\",\n        })\n    default:\n        c.JSON(http.StatusServiceUnavailable, GCTriggerResponse{\n            Started: false,\n            Message: \"GC cycle already in progress\",\n        })\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (gs *GCServer) handleStatus(c *gin.Context) {\n    stats := gs.stats.Load().(*GCStats)\n    \n    c.JSON(http.StatusOK, GCStatusResponse{\n        Running: gs.worker.IsRunning(),\n        Config:  gs.worker.GetConfig(),\n        Stats:   stats,\n    })\n}\n\nfunc (gs *GCServer) handleConfigUpdate(c *gin.Context) {\n    var req GCConfigUpdateRequest\n    if err := c.ShouldBindJSON(&req); err != nil {\n        c.JSON(http.StatusBadRequest, NewAPIError(err.Error(), \"BadRequest\", http.StatusBadRequest))\n        return\n    }\n    \n    gs.worker.UpdateConfig(req)\n    \n    c.JSON(http.StatusOK, gin.H{\"message\": \"GC configuration updated\"})\n}\n```\n\n## 6. Error Handling\n\n### 6.1 Error Types\n\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrGCWorkerNotRunning = errors.New(\"GC worker is not running\")\n    ErrGCAlreadyRunning   = errors.New(\"GC cycle already in progress\")\n    ErrInvalidConfig      = errors.New(\"invalid GC configuration\")\n    ErrNamespaceListFailed = errors.New(\"failed to list namespaces\")\n)\n```\n\n### 6.2 Error Handling Strategy\n\n| Scenario | Handling |\n|----------|----------|\n| Kubernetes API error | Log error, continue with next resource |\n| Resource already deleted | Skip, no error |\n| Cleanup failure | Log, continue deletion |\n| Batch size reached | Stop processing, report partial results |\n| Context cancelled | Stop gracefully, record partial results |\n\n## 7. Testing Strategy\n\n### 7.1 Unit Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestGCWorkerIsExpired(t *testing.T) {\n    worker := NewGCWorker(nil, nil, nil)\n    \n    // Test expired AgentRuntime\n    ar := &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:              \"test-ar\",\n            Namespace:         \"default\",\n            CreationTimestamp: metav1.Time{Time: time.Now().Add(-10 * time.Hour)},\n            DeletionTimestamp: &metav1.Time{Time: time.Now()},\n        },\n    }\n    \n    if !worker.isExpired(ar) {\n        t.Error(\"Expected expired AgentRuntime to be marked as expired\")\n    }\n    \n    // Test non-expired AgentRuntime\n    ar = &agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:              \"test-ar-2\",\n            Namespace:         \"default\",\n            CreationTimestamp: metav1.Time{Time: time.Now()},\n        },\n    }\n    \n    if worker.isExpired(ar) {\n        t.Error(\"Expected non-expired AgentRuntime to not be marked as expired\")\n    }\n}\n\nfunc TestGCWorkerGetNamespaces(t *testing.T) {\n    // Test namespace listing logic\n}\n\nfunc TestGCConfigValidation(t *testing.T) {\n    // Test config validation\n}\n```\n\n### 7.2 Test Coverage Targets\n\n| Component | Target Coverage |\n|-----------|-----------------|\n| gc.go | 80% |\n| Integration with cleanup | 75% |\n\n## 8. Configuration\n\n### 8.1 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| GC_INTERVAL | 5m | Interval between GC cycles |\n| GC_BATCH_SIZE | 50 | Maximum sandboxes processed per cycle |\n| GC_MAX_CONCURRENT_DELETES | 10 | Maximum concurrent delete operations |\n| GC_GRACE_PERIOD | 30s | Grace period before force delete |\n| GC_ENABLED | true | Enable/disable GC worker |\n\n### 8.2 Server Configuration Extension\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    \n    // GCConfig is the garbage collection configuration.\n    GCConfig *GCConfig\n}\n```\n\n## 9. Metrics\n\n### 9.1 Prometheus Metrics\n\n| Metric | Type | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| gc_cycle_duration_seconds | Histogram | Duration of GC cycle |\n| gc_sandboxes_scanned_total | Counter | Total sandboxes scanned |\n| gc_sandboxes_expired_total | Counter | Total sandboxes identified as expired |\n| gc_sandboxes_deleted_total | Counter | Total sandboxes deleted |\n| gc_sandboxes_failed_total | Counter | Total deletion failures |\n\n### 9.2 Logging\n\n| Level | Scenario |\n|-------|----------|\n| V(4) | GC cycle start/completion |\n| V(2) | Individual deletion failures |\n| V(1) | Configuration changes |\n\n## 10. Dependencies\n\n### 10.1 Internal Dependencies\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned | Client for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager (expiration.go) | Expiration detection |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager (cleanup.go) | Resource cleanup |\n\n### 10.2 External Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| k8s.io/client-go | Kubernetes client |\n| k8s.io/apimachinery | API types |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | Logging |\n| github.com/gin-gonic/gin | HTTP framework |\n\n## 11. Security Considerations\n\n### 11.1 RBAC Requirements\n\n```yaml\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"services\", \"configmaps\", \"persistentvolumeclaims\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]\n  resources: [\"namespaces\"]\n  verbs: [\"list\", \"get\"]\n```\n\n### 11.2 Safety Measures\n\n- Batch processing prevents overwhelming the API server\n- Configurable concurrency limits\n- Grace period before force deletion\n- Logging of all deletion operations\n\n## 12. References\n\n- [AR-006: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理](design.md)\n- [Expiration Logic](expiration.go)\n- [Cleanup Manager](cleanup.go)\n- [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/garbage-collection/)\n\n---\n\n# AR-038: Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-038\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: ST-1 In Progress\n\n## 1. Overview\n\nThis document provides technical implementation details for comprehensive Go unit tests in the workloadmanager module. The test suite covers all major components including WorkloadManager service, GC worker, expiration checker, graceful shutdown manager, cleanup manager, and the reconciler.\n\n## 2. Architecture Overview\n\nThe `pkg/workloadmanager` module provides resource lifecycle management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources:\n\n| Component | File | Responsibility |\n|-----------|------|----------------|\n| WorkloadManager | `service.go` | CRUD operations, sandbox operations |\n| GC Worker | `gc.go` | Periodic garbage collection (existing tests: 967 lines) |\n| Expiration Checker | `expiration.go` | TTL, idle timeout, max lifetime logic |\n| Graceful Manager | `graceful.go` | Connection draining, pre-delete hooks |\n| Cleanup Manager | `cleanup.go` | Orphaned resource cleanup |\n| K8s Client | `client.go` | Kubernetes client initialization |\n| Reconciler | `reconciler/reconciler.go` | AgentRuntime reconciliation |\n| Server | `server.go` | HTTP server initialization |\n\n### Test File Organization\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── service_test.go           # WorkloadManager interface tests\n├── client_test.go            # K8sClient initialization tests  \n├── gc_test.go                # GC worker tests (EXISTING)\n├── expiration_test.go        # Expiration checker tests (EXISTING)\n├── graceful_test.go         # Graceful manager tests\n├── cleanup_test.go          # Cleanup manager tests\n├── delete_test.go           # Delete operation tests\n├── server_test.go           # Server initialization tests\n├── batch_test.go            # Batch operations tests\n└── reconciler/\n    ├── reconciler_test.go   # Reconciler tests\n    └── errors_test.go       # Error handling tests\n```\n\n## 3. Data Structures\n\n### Core Types (`types.go`)\n```go\ntype Sandbox struct {\n    Name           string\n    Namespace      string\n    SessionID      string\n    State          SandboxState\n    CreatedAt      time.Time\n    ExpiresAt      *time.Time\n    LastActivityAt *time.Time\n    Labels         map[string]string\n    Annotations    map[string]string\n}\n\ntype SandboxState string\nconst (\n    SandboxStateUnknown  SandboxState = \"Unknown\"\n    SandboxStatePending  SandboxState = \"Pending\"\n    SandboxStateRunning  SandboxState = \"Running\"\n    SandboxStateFailed   SandboxState = \"Failed\"\n    SandboxStateDeleting SandboxState = \"Deleting\"\n)\n\ntype DeleteOptions struct {\n    GracePeriodSeconds *int64\n    Force              bool\n    LabelSelector      string\n    Preconditions      *Preconditions\n}\n```\n\n### Error Types\n```go\nvar (\n    ErrSandboxNotFound    = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n    ErrDeletionFailed     = errors.New(\"deletion failed\")\n    ErrStaleFinalizer     = errors.New(\"stale finalizer\")\n    ErrOrphanedResource   = errors.New(\"orphaned resource\")\n    ErrResourceNotFound   = errors.New(\"resource not found\")\n    ErrResourceNotDeleted = errors.New(\"resource not deleted\")\n)\n```\n\n### Configuration Types\n```go\ntype GCConfig struct {\n    GCEnabled   bool\n    GCInterval  time.Duration\n    GCBatchSize int\n}\n\ntype ExpirationConfig struct {\n    TTL         time.Duration\n    IdleTimeout time.Duration\n    MaxLifetime time.Duration\n}\n\ntype ReconcilerConfig struct {\n    SyncInterval   time.Duration\n    MaxRetries     int\n    RetryDelays    time.Duration\n    Namespace      string\n    EnableMetrics  bool\n    Workers        int\n    RateLimitBurst int\n    RateLimitQPS   float64\n}\n```\n\n## 4. API Contracts\n\n### WorkloadManager Interface (`service.go:15-39`)\n```go\ntype WorkloadManager interface {\n    // AgentRuntime CRUD\n    CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, agentRuntime, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n    GetAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n    ListAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace, opts) (*AgentRuntimeList, error)\n    UpdateAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, agentRuntime, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n    DeleteAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name, opts) error\n    GetAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, namespace, name, opts) (*AgentRuntimeStatus, error)\n    PatchAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, namespace, name, pt, data, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n    WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace, opts) (watch.Interface, error)\n    \n    // CodeInterpreter CRUD (same method pattern)\n    \n    // Sandbox operations\n    DeleteSandbox(ctx, namespace, sessionID, opts) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, namespace, sessionID) (*Sandbox, error)\n    ListSandboxes(ctx, namespace, opts) (*SandboxList, error)\n    \n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### GC Worker Interface (`gc.go:59-70`)\n```go\ntype GCWorker struct {\n    client            versioned.Interface\n    k8sClient         *kubernetes.Clientset\n    config            *GCConfig\n    stopCh            chan struct{}\n    cleanupMgr        *CleanupManager\n    expirationChecker *ExpirationChecker\n    stats             GCStats\n}\n\nfunc (g *GCWorker) Start(ctx context.Context)\nfunc (g *GCWorker) Stop()\nfunc (g *GCWorker) IsRunning() bool\nfunc (g *GCWorker) GetConfig() *GCConfig\nfunc (g *GCWorker) GetStats() GCStats\nfunc (g *GCWorker) TriggerGCCycle(ctx) *GCResult\nfunc (g *GCWorker) UpdateConfig(config *GCConfig)\n```\n\n### Reconciler Interface (`reconciler/reconciler.go:128-169`)\n```go\ntype AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n    client         versioned.Interface\n    k8sClient      *workloadmanager.K8sClient\n    scheme         *runtime.Scheme\n    recorder       record.EventRecorder\n    config         *ReconcilerConfig\n    metrics        *ReconcilerMetrics\n}\n\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ReconcileRequest) (ReconcileResult, error)\n```\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Testing Approach\n\n**Unit Testing Principles:**\n1. Use table-driven tests for parameterized scenarios\n2. Mock external Kubernetes clients using fake clientsets\n3. Test both success and error paths comprehensively\n4. Verify state transitions and side effects\n5. Ensure thread-safety for concurrent operations\n\n**Mock Strategy:**\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake` for typed clients\n- `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake` for Kubernetes clientset\n- Custom mock interfaces for complex dependencies\n\n### 5.2 Test Utilities\n\n```go\n// Test fixtures factory\nfunc newTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace, sessionID string) *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n\nfunc newTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace, sessionID string) *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n\nfunc newTestSandbox(name, namespace, sessionID string, state SandboxState) *Sandbox\n\n// Mock clients\nfunc newFakeClientset(agentRuntimes []*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, codeInterpreters []*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) versioned.Interface\n\nfunc newFakeK8sClient(pods []corev1.Pod, services []corev1.Service, configmaps []corev1.ConfigMap) *kubernetes.Clientset\n```\n\n## 6. Implementation Details\n\n### 6.1 Service Tests (`service_test.go`)\n\n| Test Function | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| `TestNewWorkloadManager` | Verify constructor creates valid instance |\n| `TestCreateAgentRuntime_*` | Create with various inputs, validation errors |\n| `TestGetAgentRuntime_*` | Found, not found, namespace errors |\n| `TestListAgentRuntimes_*` | Empty list, multiple items, pagination |\n| `TestUpdateAgentRuntime_*` | Successful update, not found, conflict |\n| `TestDeleteAgentRuntime_*` | Successful deletion, not found, graceful period |\n| `TestGetCodeInterpreter_*` | Same pattern as AgentRuntime |\n| `TestDeleteCodeInterpreter_*` | Same pattern as AgentRuntime |\n| `TestGetSandboxBySessionID_*` | AgentRuntime match, CodeInterpreter match, not found |\n| `TestListSandboxes_*` | Combined list from both resource types |\n| `TestDeleteSandbox_*` | Delete AgentRuntime, delete CodeInterpreter, not found |\n| `TestSandboxConversions` | Verify sandboxFromAgentRuntime and sandboxFromCodeInterpreter |\n\n### 6.2 Cleanup Tests (`cleanup_test.go`)\n\n| Test Function | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| `TestCleanupManager_New` | Constructor validation |\n| `TestCleanupServices_*` | Services found/not found, owner reference matching |\n| `TestCleanupConfigMaps_*` | ConfigMaps with auto-delete annotation |\n| `TestCleanupPVCs_*` | PVCs with retain policy handling |\n| `TestCleanupOrphanedResources_*` | Multiple resource types cleanup |\n| `TestCleanupAllResources_*` | Full cleanup workflow |\n| `TestFindOrphanedServices_*` | Orphan detection logic |\n\n### 6.3 Graceful Manager Tests (`graceful_test.go`)\n\n| Test Function | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| `TestGracefulManager_New` | Constructor validation |\n| `TestRegisterConnection_*` | Connection registration, concurrent access |\n| `TestUnregisterConnection_*` | Connection unregistration |\n| `TestIsDraining_*` | Drain state tracking |\n| `TestGetActiveConnections_*` | Connection count |\n| `TestWaitForConnections_*` | Timeout and success scenarios |\n| `TestExecutePreDeleteHook_*` | Hook execution, timeout handling |\n| `TestSendSIGTERM_*` | SIGTERM delivery, grace period handling |\n| `TestExecuteGracefulDelete_*` | Full graceful deletion workflow |\n\n### 6.4 Client Tests (`client_test.go`)\n\n| Test Function | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| `TestNewK8sClient_*` | In-cluster mode, kubeconfig mode, error handling |\n| `TestNewInClusterClient_*` | Successful initialization |\n| `TestExpandKubeconfigPath_*` | Tilde expansion, empty paths |\n\n### 6.5 Batch Operations Tests (`batch_test.go`)\n\n| Test Function | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| `TestBatchDelete` | Multiple resource deletion with partial failures |\n| `TestBatchList` | Combined listing with pagination |\n\n### 6.6 Server Tests (`server_test.go`)\n\n| Test Function | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| `TestNewServer` | Server initialization with config |\n| `TestServerStartStop` | Lifecycle management |\n\n### 6.7 Reconciler Tests (`reconciler/reconciler_test.go`)\n\n| Test Function | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| `TestReconciler_New` | Constructor with default config |\n| `TestReconciler_ReconcileCreate` | Create flow with pod/service/configmap |\n| `TestReconciler_ReconcileUpdate` | Update flow with change detection |\n| `TestReconciler_ReconcileDelete` | Delete flow with finalizer removal |\n| `TestReconciler_HandleError` | Error classification and retry logic |\n| `TestReconcilerMetrics_*` | Metrics collection and retrieval |\n| `TestEnsureFinalizer_*` | Finalizer addition logic |\n| `TestRemoveFinalizer_*` | Finalizer removal logic |\n\n### 6.8 Error Handling Tests (`reconciler/errors_test.go`)\n\n| Test Function | Description |\n|---------------|-------------|\n| `TestReconcilerErrorTypes` | All error type classifications |\n| `TestIsRetryable` | Retryable error detection |\n| `TestIsTerminal` | Terminal error detection |\n| `TestErrorRegistry` | Error registration and retrieval |\n| `TestNewReconcilerErrorFromK8s` | K8s error conversion |\n\n## 7. Error Handling Patterns\n\n### ReconcilerError Types (`reconciler/errors.go:10-18`)\n```go\nconst (\n    ErrorTypeTransient  ErrorType = \"Transient\"\n    ErrorTypePermanent  ErrorType = \"Permanent\"\n    ErrorTypeConflict   ErrorType = \"Conflict\"\n    ErrorTypeNotFound   ErrorType = \"NotFound\"\n    ErrorTypeValidation ErrorType = \"Validation\"\n)\n```\n\n### Error Test Cases\n```go\nfunc TestReconcilerErrorTypes(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name     string\n        err      error\n        wantType ErrorType\n        wantRetry bool\n    }{\n        {\"transient error\", NewTransientError(\"timeout\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypeTransient, true},\n        {\"permanent error\", NewPermanentError(\"quota\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypePermanent, false},\n        {\"not found\", NewNotFoundError(\"missing\", \"Pod\"), ErrorTypeNotFound, false},\n        {\"conflict\", NewConflictError(\"version\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypeConflict, true},\n        {\"validation\", NewValidationError(\"invalid\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypeValidation, false},\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n## 8. Running Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all workloadmanager tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Run with coverage\ngo test -v -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Run specific test file\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGCWorker\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n\n# Run reconciler tests\ngo test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/...\n```\n\n## 9. Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Coverage**: Minimum 70% line coverage for the module\n2. **Test Quality**: All tests use table-driven approach where applicable\n3. **Mocking**: External dependencies properly mocked (no real K8s API calls)\n4. **Error Cases**: All error paths have corresponding test cases\n5. **Concurrency**: Critical sections tested with goroutine safety\n6. **Performance**: No tests have unnecessary sleeps or long timeouts\n\n## 10. Dependencies\n\n- `testing`: Standard Go testing package\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify`: Assertions and test utilities\n- `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake`: Fake Kubernetes clientset\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake`: Fake typed clientset\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1`: Test fixtures and helpers","additions":370,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","time":{"start":1775881356627,"end":1775881356655}}}}
