{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881361632,"sessionID":"ses_2853b86e2ffeKKyacV6BUsnhng","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac713640011pMaAiksO94ca7","messageID":"msg_d7ac7059e001SRTbTz1hdhyy4v","sessionID":"ses_2853b86e2ffeKKyacV6BUsnhng","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_3d4e5e7fed57455389c3c0b5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","offset":700},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n700: ### 11.2 Safety Measures\n701: \n702: - Batch processing prevents overwhelming the API server\n703: - Configurable concurrency limits\n704: - Grace period before force deletion\n705: - Logging of all deletion operations\n706: \n707: ## 12. References\n708: \n709: - [AR-006: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理](design.md)\n710: - [Expiration Logic](expiration.go)\n711: - [Cleanup Manager](cleanup.go)\n712: - [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/garbage-collection/)\n713: \n714: ---\n715: \n716: # AR-038: Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager)\n717: \n718: - **AR ID**: AR-038\n719: - **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n720: - **Language**: Go\n721: - **Size**: L\n722: - **Status**: ST-1 In Progress\n723: \n724: ## 1. Overview\n725: \n726: This document provides technical implementation details for comprehensive Go unit tests in the workloadmanager module. The test suite covers all major components including WorkloadManager service, GC worker, expiration checker, graceful shutdown manager, cleanup manager, and the reconciler.\n727: \n728: ## 2. Architecture Overview\n729: \n730: The `pkg/workloadmanager` module provides resource lifecycle management for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources:\n731: \n732: | Component | File | Responsibility |\n733: |-----------|------|----------------|\n734: | WorkloadManager | `service.go` | CRUD operations, sandbox operations |\n735: | GC Worker | `gc.go` | Periodic garbage collection (existing tests: 967 lines) |\n736: | Expiration Checker | `expiration.go` | TTL, idle timeout, max lifetime logic |\n737: | Graceful Manager | `graceful.go` | Connection draining, pre-delete hooks |\n738: | Cleanup Manager | `cleanup.go` | Orphaned resource cleanup |\n739: | K8s Client | `client.go` | Kubernetes client initialization |\n740: | Reconciler | `reconciler/reconciler.go` | AgentRuntime reconciliation |\n741: | Server | `server.go` | HTTP server initialization |\n742: \n743: ### Test File Organization\n744: \n745: ```\n746: pkg/workloadmanager/\n747: ├── service_test.go           # WorkloadManager interface tests\n748: ├── client_test.go            # K8sClient initialization tests  \n749: ├── gc_test.go                # GC worker tests (EXISTING)\n750: ├── expiration_test.go        # Expiration checker tests (EXISTING)\n751: ├── graceful_test.go         # Graceful manager tests\n752: ├── cleanup_test.go          # Cleanup manager tests\n753: ├── delete_test.go           # Delete operation tests\n754: ├── server_test.go           # Server initialization tests\n755: ├── batch_test.go            # Batch operations tests\n756: └── reconciler/\n757:     ├── reconciler_test.go   # Reconciler tests\n758:     └── errors_test.go       # Error handling tests\n759: ```\n760: \n761: ## 3. Data Structures\n762: \n763: ### Core Types (`types.go`)\n764: ```go\n765: type Sandbox struct {\n766:     Name           string\n767:     Namespace      string\n768:     SessionID      string\n769:     State          SandboxState\n770:     CreatedAt      time.Time\n771:     ExpiresAt      *time.Time\n772:     LastActivityAt *time.Time\n773:     Labels         map[string]string\n774:     Annotations    map[string]string\n775: }\n776: \n777: type SandboxState string\n778: const (\n779:     SandboxStateUnknown  SandboxState = \"Unknown\"\n780:     SandboxStatePending  SandboxState = \"Pending\"\n781:     SandboxStateRunning  SandboxState = \"Running\"\n782:     SandboxStateFailed   SandboxState = \"Failed\"\n783:     SandboxStateDeleting SandboxState = \"Deleting\"\n784: )\n785: \n786: type DeleteOptions struct {\n787:     GracePeriodSeconds *int64\n788:     Force              bool\n789:     LabelSelector      string\n790:     Preconditions      *Preconditions\n791: }\n792: ```\n793: \n794: ### Error Types\n795: ```go\n796: var (\n797:     ErrSandboxNotFound    = errors.New(\"sandbox not found\")\n798:     ErrDeletionFailed     = errors.New(\"deletion failed\")\n799:     ErrStaleFinalizer     = errors.New(\"stale finalizer\")\n800:     ErrOrphanedResource   = errors.New(\"orphaned resource\")\n801:     ErrResourceNotFound   = errors.New(\"resource not found\")\n802:     ErrResourceNotDeleted = errors.New(\"resource not deleted\")\n803: )\n804: ```\n805: \n806: ### Configuration Types\n807: ```go\n808: type GCConfig struct {\n809:     GCEnabled   bool\n810:     GCInterval  time.Duration\n811:     GCBatchSize int\n812: }\n813: \n814: type ExpirationConfig struct {\n815:     TTL         time.Duration\n816:     IdleTimeout time.Duration\n817:     MaxLifetime time.Duration\n818: }\n819: \n820: type ReconcilerConfig struct {\n821:     SyncInterval   time.Duration\n822:     MaxRetries     int\n823:     RetryDelays    time.Duration\n824:     Namespace      string\n825:     EnableMetrics  bool\n826:     Workers        int\n827:     RateLimitBurst int\n828:     RateLimitQPS   float64\n829: }\n830: ```\n831: \n832: ## 4. API Contracts\n833: \n834: ### WorkloadManager Interface (`service.go:15-39`)\n835: ```go\n836: type WorkloadManager interface {\n837:     // AgentRuntime CRUD\n838:     CreateAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, agentRuntime, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n839:     GetAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n840:     ListAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace, opts) (*AgentRuntimeList, error)\n841:     UpdateAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, agentRuntime, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n842:     DeleteAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name, opts) error\n843:     GetAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, namespace, name, opts) (*AgentRuntimeStatus, error)\n844:     PatchAgentRuntimeStatus(ctx, namespace, name, pt, data, opts) (*AgentRuntime, error)\n845:     WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace, opts) (watch.Interface, error)\n846:     \n847:     // CodeInterpreter CRUD (same method pattern)\n848:     \n849:     // Sandbox operations\n850:     DeleteSandbox(ctx, namespace, sessionID, opts) error\n851:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, namespace, sessionID) (*Sandbox, error)\n852:     ListSandboxes(ctx, namespace, opts) (*SandboxList, error)\n853:     \n854:     Close() error\n855: }\n856: ```\n857: \n858: ### GC Worker Interface (`gc.go:59-70`)\n859: ```go\n860: type GCWorker struct {\n861:     client            versioned.Interface\n862:     k8sClient         *kubernetes.Clientset\n863:     config            *GCConfig\n864:     stopCh            chan struct{}\n865:     cleanupMgr        *CleanupManager\n866:     expirationChecker *ExpirationChecker\n867:     stats             GCStats\n868: }\n869: \n870: func (g *GCWorker) Start(ctx context.Context)\n871: func (g *GCWorker) Stop()\n872: func (g *GCWorker) IsRunning() bool\n873: func (g *GCWorker) GetConfig() *GCConfig\n874: func (g *GCWorker) GetStats() GCStats\n875: func (g *GCWorker) TriggerGCCycle(ctx) *GCResult\n876: func (g *GCWorker) UpdateConfig(config *GCConfig)\n877: ```\n878: \n879: ### Reconciler Interface (`reconciler/reconciler.go:128-169`)\n880: ```go\n881: type AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n882:     client         versioned.Interface\n883:     k8sClient      *workloadmanager.K8sClient\n884:     scheme         *runtime.Scheme\n885:     recorder       record.EventRecorder\n886:     config         *ReconcilerConfig\n887:     metrics        *ReconcilerMetrics\n888: }\n889: \n890: func (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ReconcileRequest) (ReconcileResult, error)\n891: ```\n892: \n893: ## 5. Testing Strategy\n894: \n895: ### 5.1 Testing Approach\n896: \n897: **Unit Testing Principles:**\n898: 1. Use table-driven tests for parameterized scenarios\n899: 2. Mock external Kubernetes clients using fake clientsets\n900: 3. Test both success and error paths comprehensively\n901: 4. Verify state transitions and side effects\n902: 5. Ensure thread-safety for concurrent operations\n903: \n904: **Mock Strategy:**\n905: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake` for typed clients\n906: - `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake` for Kubernetes clientset\n907: - Custom mock interfaces for complex dependencies\n908: \n909: ### 5.2 Test Utilities\n910: \n911: ```go\n912: // Test fixtures factory\n913: func newTestAgentRuntime(name, namespace, sessionID string) *agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n914: \n915: func newTestCodeInterpreter(name, namespace, sessionID string) *agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n916: \n917: func newTestSandbox(name, namespace, sessionID string, state SandboxState) *Sandbox\n918: \n919: // Mock clients\n920: func newFakeClientset(agentRuntimes []*agentcubev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, codeInterpreters []*agentcubev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) versioned.Interface\n921: \n922: func newFakeK8sClient(pods []corev1.Pod, services []corev1.Service, configmaps []corev1.ConfigMap) *kubernetes.Clientset\n923: ```\n924: \n925: ## 6. Implementation Details\n926: \n927: ### 6.1 Service Tests (`service_test.go`)\n928: \n929: | Test Function | Description |\n930: |---------------|-------------|\n931: | `TestNewWorkloadManager` | Verify constructor creates valid instance |\n932: | `TestCreateAgentRuntime_*` | Create with various inputs, validation errors |\n933: | `TestGetAgentRuntime_*` | Found, not found, namespace errors |\n934: | `TestListAgentRuntimes_*` | Empty list, multiple items, pagination |\n935: | `TestUpdateAgentRuntime_*` | Successful update, not found, conflict |\n936: | `TestDeleteAgentRuntime_*` | Successful deletion, not found, graceful period |\n937: | `TestGetCodeInterpreter_*` | Same pattern as AgentRuntime |\n938: | `TestDeleteCodeInterpreter_*` | Same pattern as AgentRuntime |\n939: | `TestGetSandboxBySessionID_*` | AgentRuntime match, CodeInterpreter match, not found |\n940: | `TestListSandboxes_*` | Combined list from both resource types |\n941: | `TestDeleteSandbox_*` | Delete AgentRuntime, delete CodeInterpreter, not found |\n942: | `TestSandboxConversions` | Verify sandboxFromAgentRuntime and sandboxFromCodeInterpreter |\n943: \n944: ### 6.2 Cleanup Tests (`cleanup_test.go`)\n945: \n946: | Test Function | Description |\n947: |---------------|-------------|\n948: | `TestCleanupManager_New` | Constructor validation |\n949: | `TestCleanupServices_*` | Services found/not found, owner reference matching |\n950: | `TestCleanupConfigMaps_*` | ConfigMaps with auto-delete annotation |\n951: | `TestCleanupPVCs_*` | PVCs with retain policy handling |\n952: | `TestCleanupOrphanedResources_*` | Multiple resource types cleanup |\n953: | `TestCleanupAllResources_*` | Full cleanup workflow |\n954: | `TestFindOrphanedServices_*` | Orphan detection logic |\n955: \n956: ### 6.3 Graceful Manager Tests (`graceful_test.go`)\n957: \n958: | Test Function | Description |\n959: |---------------|-------------|\n960: | `TestGracefulManager_New` | Constructor validation |\n961: | `TestRegisterConnection_*` | Connection registration, concurrent access |\n962: | `TestUnregisterConnection_*` | Connection unregistration |\n963: | `TestIsDraining_*` | Drain state tracking |\n964: | `TestGetActiveConnections_*` | Connection count |\n965: | `TestWaitForConnections_*` | Timeout and success scenarios |\n966: | `TestExecutePreDeleteHook_*` | Hook execution, timeout handling |\n967: | `TestSendSIGTERM_*` | SIGTERM delivery, grace period handling |\n968: | `TestExecuteGracefulDelete_*` | Full graceful deletion workflow |\n969: \n970: ### 6.4 Client Tests (`client_test.go`)\n971: \n972: | Test Function | Description |\n973: |---------------|-------------|\n974: | `TestNewK8sClient_*` | In-cluster mode, kubeconfig mode, error handling |\n975: | `TestNewInClusterClient_*` | Successful initialization |\n976: | `TestExpandKubeconfigPath_*` | Tilde expansion, empty paths |\n977: \n978: ### 6.5 Batch Operations Tests (`batch_test.go`)\n979: \n980: | Test Function | Description |\n981: |---------------|-------------|\n982: | `TestBatchDelete` | Multiple resource deletion with partial failures |\n983: | `TestBatchList` | Combined listing with pagination |\n984: \n985: ### 6.6 Server Tests (`server_test.go`)\n986: \n987: | Test Function | Description |\n988: |---------------|-------------|\n989: | `TestNewServer` | Server initialization with config |\n990: | `TestServerStartStop` | Lifecycle management |\n991: \n992: ### 6.7 Reconciler Tests (`reconciler/reconciler_test.go`)\n993: \n994: | Test Function | Description |\n995: |---------------|-------------|\n996: | `TestReconciler_New` | Constructor with default config |\n997: | `TestReconciler_ReconcileCreate` | Create flow with pod/service/configmap |\n998: | `TestReconciler_ReconcileUpdate` | Update flow with change detection |\n999: | `TestReconciler_ReconcileDelete` | Delete flow with finalizer removal |\n1000: | `TestReconciler_HandleError` | Error classification and retry logic |\n1001: | `TestReconcilerMetrics_*` | Metrics collection and retrieval |\n1002: | `TestEnsureFinalizer_*` | Finalizer addition logic |\n1003: | `TestRemoveFinalizer_*` | Finalizer removal logic |\n1004: \n1005: ### 6.8 Error Handling Tests (`reconciler/errors_test.go`)\n1006: \n1007: | Test Function | Description |\n1008: |---------------|-------------|\n1009: | `TestReconcilerErrorTypes` | All error type classifications |\n1010: | `TestIsRetryable` | Retryable error detection |\n1011: | `TestIsTerminal` | Terminal error detection |\n1012: | `TestErrorRegistry` | Error registration and retrieval |\n1013: | `TestNewReconcilerErrorFromK8s` | K8s error conversion |\n1014: \n1015: ## 7. Error Handling Patterns\n1016: \n1017: ### ReconcilerError Types (`reconciler/errors.go:10-18`)\n1018: ```go\n1019: const (\n1020:     ErrorTypeTransient  ErrorType = \"Transient\"\n1021:     ErrorTypePermanent  ErrorType = \"Permanent\"\n1022:     ErrorTypeConflict   ErrorType = \"Conflict\"\n1023:     ErrorTypeNotFound   ErrorType = \"NotFound\"\n1024:     ErrorTypeValidation ErrorType = \"Validation\"\n1025: )\n1026: ```\n1027: \n1028: ### Error Test Cases\n1029: ```go\n1030: func TestReconcilerErrorTypes(t *testing.T) {\n1031:     tests := []struct {\n1032:         name     string\n1033:         err      error\n1034:         wantType ErrorType\n1035:         wantRetry bool\n1036:     }{\n1037:         {\"transient error\", NewTransientError(\"timeout\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypeTransient, true},\n1038:         {\"permanent error\", NewPermanentError(\"quota\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypePermanent, false},\n1039:         {\"not found\", NewNotFoundError(\"missing\", \"Pod\"), ErrorTypeNotFound, false},\n1040:         {\"conflict\", NewConflictError(\"version\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypeConflict, true},\n1041:         {\"validation\", NewValidationError(\"invalid\", \"Pod\", nil), ErrorTypeValidation, false},\n1042:     }\n1043:     // ...\n1044: }\n1045: ```\n1046: \n1047: ## 8. Running Tests\n1048: \n1049: ```bash\n1050: # Run all workloadmanager tests\n1051: go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n1052: \n1053: # Run with coverage\n1054: go test -v -cover ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n1055: \n1056: # Run specific test file\n1057: go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGCWorker\n1058: \n1059: # Run with race detector\n1060: go test -race ./pkg/workloadmanager/...\n1061: \n1062: # Run reconciler tests\n1063: go test -v ./pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/...\n1064: ```\n1065: \n1066: ## 9. Acceptance Criteria\n1067: \n1068: 1. **Coverage**: Minimum 70% line coverage for the module\n1069: 2. **Test Quality**: All tests use table-driven approach where applicable\n1070: 3. **Mocking**: External dependencies properly mocked (no real K8s API calls)\n1071: 4. **Error Cases**: All error paths have corresponding test cases\n1072: 5. **Concurrency**: Critical sections tested with goroutine safety\n1073: 6. **Performance**: No tests have unnecessary sleeps or long timeouts\n1074: \n1075: ## 10. Dependencies\n1076: \n1077: - `testing`: Standard Go testing package\n1078: - `github.com/stretchr/testify`: Assertions and test utilities\n1079: - `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes/fake`: Fake Kubernetes clientset\n1080: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/fake`: Fake typed clientset\n1081: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1`: Test fixtures and helpers\n\n(End of file - total 1081 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"### 11.2 Safety Measures\n\n- Batch processing prevents overwhelming the API server\n- Configurable concurrency limits\n- Grace period before force deletion\n- Logging of all deletion operations\n\n## 12. References\n\n- [AR-006: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理](design.md)\n- [Expiration Logic](expiration.go)\n- [Cleanup Manager](cleanup.go)\n- [Kubernetes Garbage Collection](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/garbage-collection/)\n\n---\n\n# AR-038: Go Unit Tests (workloadmanager)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-038\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/design.md","time":{"start":1775881361621,"end":1775881361629}}}}
